body: Hey Folks, I noticed at the bottom the email I said we were going to do Veterans park on Sunday. Correction is we are going to stay in Laguna Beach. I will see how you guys do, and we might do Crescent Bay on Sunday. It's a really cool dive there, lots of life and if we are lucky, we will see some sea lions. Please remember to bring your log books so we can fill them out. If you do have any questions please feel free to contact me. Regards, Josue From: Josue Lopez <josuelopez222@hotmail.com> Sent: Wednesday, October 11, 2023 11:43 PM To: daniellovelogk22@gmail.com <daniellovelogk22@gmail.com>; crystal.k2029@gmail.com <crystal.k2029@gmail.com>; ivanaaortiz@gmail.com <ivanaaortiz@gmail.com>; jeremy.t.prince13@gmail.com <jeremy.t.prince13@gmail.com>; Jana Frazier <janabanana1389@gmail.com>; Thomas B <thomasbacalja@gmail.com>; lboncich@gmail.com <lboncich@gmail.com> Subject: Re: Oct 14th and 15th Beach Days (Special Request) *******Can one of you please pick up the PADI Pics from the shop for me on Friday when you pick up you gear.******* ******************* Also please respond to this email so I know everyone is on the same page******************** Hello Scuba divers(in training):), Our projected dive site for Saturday will be Shaw's cove in Laguna Beach. Please plan to pick up your gear from Pacific Wilderness on Friday before 5:00pm to allow time for fitting your gear. Be sure you set-up and test all your gear, including testing your regulators and BCD, at the shop before putting it in your car and leaving. YOU ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR YOUR GEAR. Finding an issue at the dive site may prevent you from participating in these dives and result in you having to reschedule. As a reminder, you will have to upgrade to integrated weights rather than a weight belt and / or a computer rather than the standard set of gauges with depth and air pressure. Remember we opted to use the computers so we didn't have to take the recreational dive planer test. It is important to remember your personal gear (gloves, boots, snorkel, mask, fins), swimsuit, towel, change of clothes, water, snacks, and sunscreen. Don't forget, we need 2 copies of a passport sized photo so if you only submitted 1, bring them in for this weekend. Find local businesses, view maps and get driving directions in Google Maps. www.google.com Please try to park as close as possible to the top of the stairs. When you get to the beach set up all of your gear and stage all your personal gear so we can all be on the same page to gear up. Once you are all ready to go, we will meet up at the top of the stairs to go over what we are going to do. On Saturday, be ready for the dive briefing no later than 6:30am (Meet-up time). We'll aim to be in the water for 7:00am (Start-up time) for the first dive. Plan to bring your tanks back to Pacific Wilderness after the dive to refill your tanks. Or we can fill your tanks at the local dive shop on your dime as to save you the drive and probably be cheaper than the gasoline. If you feel you can't locate me, call me at (949)309-1290. Ill be in a Silver Volvo Let me know if you have any questions. Looking forward to diving with all of you! Sunday will most likely be the same beach at Veterans Park Josue Lopez #254617 (949)309-1290 PS. Jana, I'm just assuming you are going to be my Divemaster, If I'm wrong please disregard. Thanks, you are the best! Welcome to your Pacific Wilderness PADI Open-Water Diver Course! My name is _Josue Lopez__, Ill be your PADI Open Water Dive Instructor for your class beginning September 9th 2023 Please read the ENTIRE email as it will help us avoid misunderstandings and/or problems. Prior to Starting Your PADI Open Water Class with Pacific Wilderness (at Least 1 Week Prior): Visit our San Pedro Dive Center to Pick-up your OW Materials: Including Book, Tables, Log & DVD / USB Drive. Please Note: Materials will run $150 but are completely FREE if you purchase ALL 5 Pieces of the Required Basic Gear at ONE TIME here at Pacific Wilderness. Prices are GUARANTEED to be the Best. Get fitted & Purchase your Basic Snorkeling Gear at our San Pedro Location. Read your Open Water Book and Complete All 5 Knowledge Reviews. View your DVD in its entirety. Complete your Medical release. If you answer ANY question on the Medical Form "Yes" you will need to get a signed release from your Doctor PRIOR to Class. Click for Medical form. Weekend #1 (Classroom & Pool) What to bring both Saturday & Sunday: Please have the Medical Questionnaire filled out. If you answered "yes" to any question, you would need to have the Medical Release form signed by a physician PRIOR to the first class. () Basic gear (fins, mask, snorkel, boots, and gloves). This needs to be proper SCUBA type gear for cold-water use. If you have questions, please contact the shop. Better yet - just buy it at Pacific Wilderness. I assure you their pricing is BETTER than online, and all items need to be fitted to your body. Additionally, when you buy at the shop, the $150 PADI Materials package is FREE! Basic Gear Packages begin at $185 complete, & you have the option to exchange gear during your pool session & we have a Lowest Price Guarantee. Bathing suit and towel for use in the Pool. Pool is heated to a comfortable 85 degrees. Copies of the completed knowledge reviews at the end of each chapter of your PADI book. Please also bring the book along with everything that came in the Book package + Pen & Note Paper. 2 passport style" photos (1  wide X 2  H). Printed on your printer is fine. No Sunglasses please. You can bring a lunch or there are fast food options close to the shop. The classroom has FREE Coffee & Bottled Water available every day. Here are some more details about the first two days of class & pool and what we will be doing. We will start at 9:00 am each day. Its a good idea to be parked in the shops back parking lot no later than 8:45 am. Please pull all the way forward if you are in one of the Tandem Parking spots. Finishing time depends on you and your classmates mastering the dive skills and your comprehension of the academic portion in the classroom. Either way, plan on being at the shop all day on both days (9 am to 5 pm). When you get to the shop, please park behind the store or on side streets (17th or 18th). The street out front (Pacific Avenue) is only 1-hour parking. The stores Parking Lot in back fits 16 cars, so if you arrive at about 8:30 am, you will likely be guaranteed a prime parking spot. This will make loading & unloading gear much easier  You will need to have reasonable swimming skills, so please be comfortable in the water. :) To demonstrate that you are comfortable in the water, we have two quick tests in the pool. The 1st test will be a 200-yard swim, non-stop, without aid, or 300 yards with mask, fins, and snorkel. There is NO TIME LIMIT, so dont worry, we just need to assess your skill level. 2nd test will be to float/tread water for 10 minutes without aid. If you do not know how to swim, please take a class at the YMCA prior to starting your class. This is a SCUBA class, not a SWIM Class . Please come to class prepared. Bring everything that came in the PADI Book package and please have all the academic portions done. This means to read your entire book, watch the video/DVD/USB Drive, and answer all the Knowledge Review questions. There are 5 Knowledge Reviews, one at the end of each chapter. Please make a copy of each one of these completed Knowledge Reviews and bring them with you to class. I will need the copies for your Student Record Folder (SRF). Also, please read & review the RDP  recreational Dive Planner Booklet and practice doing the tables. You will need to understand the Dive Tables as part of your training and final testing. During class, you will be taking 4 multiple choice quizzes and a final exam to finish the academic portion here at the shop. This will show that you understand Diving Concepts and Physics. So please be prepared. For the dive skills portion in the pool, you will need to complete 5 dives. Each of these dives has a set of skills prescribed, each one progressing on the last. Starting in the shallow end (3.5 ft.) & ending in the deep end (12 ft.). Weekend #2 (Ocean Dives) Friday: The day before your Local Beach Dives, youll need to come into our San Pedro Location to pick up your SCUBA Rental Gear (One Weekend of Rental Gear Included in the class). Plan on about 45 minutes for fitting, so please dont show up at 10 minutes till closing (which is 7 pm). If you cant make it Friday to pick up Rental Gear and wish to pick it up earlier, you will be charged a daily rate for the extra day(s). You may also arrange a pre-fitting Sunday during Class/Pool break and have another Student in your Class pick the gear up for you on Friday as scheduled. Youll need a Full Pack which includes Regulator System, Tank, BC, Weight Belt & Weights, Wetsuit & Hood. Youll also need to pack your Basic Snorkeling Gear for the Dives as well. Prep your Gear Friday night when you get home and prepare for some weekend Fun! You will be offered the option to upgrade your regulator System to include a computer. In which case you will not need to supply a dive watch for the dives. Should you choose the upgrade, its only $15 for the weekend & is completely OPTIONAL. You will also be offered the option to upgrade to a weight integrated BC (More Comfortable) for $15 for the weekend, this is also completely OPTIONAL. Saturday: You'll get up Early to meet with fellow students and your Instructor(s) at the Local Beach Diving spot at 7:00 am or 8:00 am (Instructor will advise). When you arrive at the Beach, youll find parking and have a stack of Quarters (about $10 worth) and/or a Credit Card with you to feed the meter. Following your two dives, youll make your way back to Pacific Wilderness for Air Re-Fills on your Tanks (Included in Class) in preparation for Sundays final two dives. You can then clean up if you wish and have the afternoon off to enjoy the rest of your day. Sunday: You'll get up Early to meet with fellow students and your Instructor(s) at the Local Beach Diving spot at 7 or 8 am again. When you arrive at the Beach, youll find parking and have a stack of Quarters (about $10 worth) and/or a Credit Card with you to feed the meter (You know the drill). Following your two dives, youll make your way back to Pacific Wilderness to rinse & return your rental gear then hang out with fellow student graduates! Please read the shops cancellation and makeup policy outlined online & contained in your OpenWater packet as well. The classes build on each other, so if you miss a class, you will not be able to go to the next class until the class you missed is made up. Instructors do not work for FREE, so please respect our time and show up on time & be prepared. Please let me know when you receive this email. Please Contact me (Not the Dive Shop) if you have any questions during your Class. Instructor Name: __Josue I. Lopez___ E-mail: _josuelopez222@hotmail.com__ Phone (Text): (949)309-1290____

Dropped alone without support, Snake has arrived in the jungles of the USSR to finish what his mentor started. Fortunately, he might have finally found an ally who can help him find the answers he needs to break free. Embark on two terrifying journeys across parallel worlds as the accomplished FBI agent Saga Anderson and Alan Wake himself in this search for solace and sanity. Define your own brand of justice as you fulfil your prime directives and bring order to the crime-ridden streets of Old Detroit. Coming to PC Game Pass 26 April. FAME, FORTUNE AND FRENZY Enter the dynamic virtual arenas of THE FINALS, where every element of your environment is a potential tool for more prestige.
